      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean \"misguided\" is a pretty strong word for a policy that many people think keeps them safe. if someone is arguing that strict sentencing actually deters people from committing crimes, aren't they just looking at the data on deterrence? why is that considered \"misguided\" instead of just a different way of looking at public safety?",
