      "role": "user",
      "content": "so you're saying the deterrence argument is basically just \"anecdotal\" and \"simplistic\"? that feels like you're dismissing a huge part of the debate as just being wrong. if the research is \"weak,\" doesn't that mean it's still a valid perspective for people who prioritize immediate public safety over long-term sociological goals? why can't it just be seen as a legitimate, if different, viewpoint?",
